    "asOf": "2003-03-12",
    "date": "2006-10-12T15:41:24Z",
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a special amortization tax deduction for up to $5 million of the intangible property acquired from an eligible small business (i.e., a business with gross receipts not exceeding $5 million for the three preceding taxable years) after December 31, 2002."
